1. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a system that uses deep learning and a neural network to automate theorem proving, which falls under the domain of AI. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses a neural network to augment the bandit algorithm and sequence-to-sequence model for action enumeration, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
3. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) - The paper specifically focuses on automated theorem proving in higher order logic, which falls under the domain of logic in computer science. 
4. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper explores the formalism of the Metamath language, which could be considered a programming language. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes a system for automated theorem proving, which could be considered a software engineering problem.
